            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The einsteinium isotopes used for these studies were",
                "obtained from the Transuranium Element Production",
                "Program at Oak Ridge National Laboratory. The",
                "einsteinium was chemically separated from other",
                "actinide and fission product elements by elution with",
                "a-hydroxyisobutryric acid from a Dowex-50 cation",
                "exchange resin column(ammonium form). After removal of",
                "small aliquots for alpha counting, the purified sources",
                " of einsteinium were deposited on platinum discs."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 17-cm3 coaxial lithium-drifted germanium",
                "detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The catcher foils were dissolved in the",
                "presence of carriers, specific fission products were",
                "radiochemically purified and thick samples(~10mg/cm2)",
                "were mounted for beta counting in calibrated low",
                "background (0.4 count/min) counting equipment. The",
                "radioactive purity of each sample was verified by",
                "following its decay over several half lives. The",
                "observed counting rate for each fission product was",
                "corrected for chemical yield, counter efficiency,",
                "decay, genetic relationships and degree of saturation",
                "to give the relative saturation activity A which is",
                "proportional to the fission yield. In several",
                "experiments the activities of various fission",
                "products were determined without chemical separation",
                "by measuring the gamma-ray spectrum from the catcher",
                "foils with a lithium-drifted germanium detector.",
                "These spectra were analyzed with a computer program",
                "to determine the relative intensity of the various",
                "gamma-rays."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The relative fission yields determined by these",
                "methods were placed on an absolute basis by",
                "normalizing the final mass-yield curves to 200% total",
                "yield."
              ]
            }
          ],
